<title>
Windshield Dimensions
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
The dimensions with “*” are distance to same point on opposite side.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
In principle, body dimensions in the figure below are symmetrical. Adopt the dimension for the opposite side if the dimension is not mentioned in the figure below.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Use point 36 as datum point to check symmetry of body dimensions.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Measure distance between point 36 and each point on vehicle left side and vehicle right side for symmetry check.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The number with “&#248;” is circle diameter and measurement unit is “mm”.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
